# Unified Social Media OS - Architecture & Workflow Documentation

This document explains the technical architecture, component structure, security model, and complete integration workflow of the **Unified Social Media OS Dashboard** application.

---

## 1. System Architecture Overview

The system is split into three core layers: the React Client (Frontend), the Node.js API (Backend), and the MongoDB database, interacting with Google's OAuth 2.0 server.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as User Browser
    participant FE as React Frontend (:3000)
    participant BE as Express Backend (:5000)
    participant DB as MongoDB (Atlas)
    participant Google as Google OAuth Server

    %% Registration / Login
    User->>FE: Fill Login/Signup Form
    FE->>BE: POST /auth/login (or /register)
    BE->>DB: Verify / Create User
    DB-->>BE: User Record
    BE-->>FE: Return JWT & User Object
    Note over FE: Store JWT in localStorage

    %% Initiating OAuth
    User->>FE: Click "Connect YouTube"
    FE->>User: redirect to backend /auth/youtube?token=<JWT>
    User->>BE: GET /auth/youtube?token=<JWT>
    Note over BE: Verify JWT from query param
    Note over BE: Store random state in pendingStates Map
    BE-->>User: 302 Redirect to accounts.google.com
    User->>Google: Navigate to Consent Screen

    %% Google Consent Screen
    Google-->>User: Display scopes consent prompt
    User->>Google: Approve permissions
    Google-->>User: 302 Redirect to backend callback with ?code=&state=

    %% Callback Flow
    User->>BE: GET /auth/youtube/callback?code=<AUTH_CODE>&state=<STATE>
    Note over BE: Verify state match (CSRF check)
    BE->>Google: POST /token (exchange code for tokens)
    Google-->>BE: Return Access & Refresh Tokens
    BE->>Google: GET /channels (fetch platform username)
    Google-->>BE: Return YouTube Channel Title
    Note over BE: Encrypt tokens via AES-256-CBC
    BE->>DB: Upsert account in socialAccounts array
    DB-->>BE: Save success
    BE-->>User: 302 Redirect to frontend /settings?connected=youtube

    %% Frontend Verification
    User->>FE: Load /settings?connected=youtube
    Note over FE: Trigger refreshUser() Context API call
    FE->>BE: GET /auth/me (with Authorization Header)
    BE-->>FE: Return updated User profiles
    FE-->>User: Show success toast & redirect to Dashboard
```

